The '''Emperor's Citadel''', also known as '''Imperial Citadel''', was the fortress that was located on the elusive [[Deep Core/Legends|Deep Core]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Byss/Legends|Byss]]. A large black and red-tinted tower at the centre of the [[Imperial control sector]] that contained a [[Imperial throne room (Byss Citadel)|throne room]] of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. In [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]], the reborn [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Darth Sidious|Palpatine]] used the [[Throne/Legends|throne]] when he reigned over the [[Dark Empire]].

==Description==
This great black and red-tinted tower contained the personal quarters and offices of Palpatine and his officials. The [[Imperial throne room (Byss Citadel)|Emperor's throne room]], [[Clone Labs]] which kept his collection of clone bodies, [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] [[Sith alchemy/Legends|Sith alchemical]] laboratories, the [[Great Hall (Byss)|Great Hall]], a war room, and libraries filled with dark side tomes were also located within the Emperor's Citadel.

It was in this citadel on his throne world that Palpatine experimented on a wide range of life with his dark side powers, even sentient beings. There were also sublevel breeding facilities which birthed the deadly [[Chrysalide]] [[Rancor/Legends|rancors]]. Elite [[Imperial Sovereign Protector]]s&mdash;the best of the [[Emperor's Royal Guard/Legends|Imperial Royal Guard]]&mdash;were also stationed at the citadel. He kept his cloning facilities within the palace to make it easier and faster to resurrect himself when needed.

There were also a series of training rooms in the citadel compound where Palpatine trained his [[Dark side adept/Legends|Dark Side Adepts]] and a few chosen [[Inquisitorius/Legends|Inquisitors]]. He also kept several [[Holocron/Legends|Jedi]] and [[Sith holocron/Legends|Sith holocrons]] which he had acquired. The [[Emperor's throne room]] was also capable of serving as a military command center which he used to supervise the [[World Devastator]] [[Attack on Mon Calamari|assault]] on [[Dac/Legends|Mon Calamari]].

==History==
[[File:The_Emperors_Citadel.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The Emperor's Citadel in [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]].]]
The citadel was constructed shortly after Palpatine rose to power, following the end of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. The [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] used [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]] from many conquered worlds&mdash;including [[Gamorr/Legends|Gamorr]], [[Toydaria/Legends|Toydaria]], and [[Utapau/Legends|Utapau]]&mdash;to complete the citadel quickly.

Reborn in a [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] body after his death aboard the [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]], Palpatine brought [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] to the citadel, and was able to convert the [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]]. Later, [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] and [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] breached the citadel's defenses to rescue Luke. The citadel was attacked by [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] agents through the use of sabotaged [[X-1 Viper]]s during the [[Battle of the Emperor's Citadel]], but the attack was thwarted through the use of alchemically-altered [[Chrysalide]]s. The citadel was destroyed along with the rest of Byss in [[11 ABY/Legends|11 ABY]] when the ''[[Eclipse II]]'' rammed into the [[Galaxy Gun]].

==Equipment==
The Citadel was guarded by three [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] [[Legion/Legends|legions]] and 600 [[Imperial Sentinel]]s; Chrysalides, [[Dark side adept/Legends|Dark Side Adepts]], [[Hunter-Killer probot]]s and [[Scorpenek annihilator droid/Legends|Scorpenek annihilator droids]] also patrolled the area. Its equipment included [[HoloNet/Legends|HoloNet]] stations, battle computers and command rooms, the [[Clone Labs]], prisons, a throne room, the [[Great Hall (Byss)|Great Hall]], a meeting area for the [[Imperial Ruling Council/Legends|Imperial Inner Circle]], libraries, museums, gardens and [[Gladiator/Legends|gladiator]] combat arenas.

==Behind the scenes==
In the [[The Star Wars rough draft|rough draft]] of the script for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']], the [[Imperial City of Alderaan|Imperial City]] was to have been located on the top of an impossibly high spire, far above the surface of the capital world.<ref name="Making of">''[[The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film]]''</ref> This would inspire [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|The Empire Strikes Back]], but may also have served as an inspiration for the Citadel on Byss.

